{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> λᾰλ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>talk, chat, prattle</b>, ἕπου καὶ μὴ λάλει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 1058, compare “V.” 1135; ἡ μὲν χελιδὼν τὸ θέρος.. λαλεῖ 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 208; λαλεῖς.. ἀμελήσας ἀποκρίνασθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 287d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>dative</i>, <b>talk to</b> one, λαλῶν ἐν ταῖς ὁδοῖς σεαυτῷ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 348; αὑτοῖς 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 11; πρὸς αὑτούς 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 9.10; λ. περί τινος 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 2, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 627; ὑπέρ τινος 3rd c.BC: Posidippus Comicus 26.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to λέγω, λαλεῖν ἄριστος, ἀδυνατώτατος λέγειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 95 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λαλῶν μὲν.., λέγων δέ.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.118 (assuming variant); λαλεῖν τι ἡμῖν ὅπως ἂν ἡμᾶς ὕπνος λάβῃ 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 7.10: hence, \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> generally, <b>talk, speak</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 110 (variant for{λακεῖν}); καινὴν διάλεκτον λ. 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 171; Ἀττικιστὶ λ. 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 195.4. with _metaphorically_, ζωγραφία λαλοῦσα (of poetry), opposed to ποίησις σιωπῶσα (of painting), 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus cited in 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.346f. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>talk of</b>, τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus “fragment” 5.2; ἀλλήλαις λαλέουσι τεὸν γάμον αἱ κυπάρισσοι 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 27.58; ἅμαξαν “Stoicorum Veterum Fragmenta” 2.92 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, πρᾶγμα κατ᾽ ἀγορὰν λαλούμενον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 578. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> in later writers, ={λέγω}, <b>speak</b>, λαλεῖ οὐθὲν τῶν ἄλλων ζῴων πλὴν ἀνθρώπου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 899a1: frequently in LXX, LXX.Gen.12.4, +others; βασιλέως ἐναντίον 2nd c.BC: Ezekiel Poeta Judaeus “Exagoge - Mnemosyne” 118; πρός τινα NT.Act.3.22, compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Vit.Auct.” 3, etc.; περὶ τῆς λέξεως 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ ποιημάτων” 5.32, compare “Rh.” 1.189 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus, +others\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; χειρσὶν ἅπαντα λαλήσας, of a pantomime, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 14.2124: _absolutely_, εἴ τι μὴ λίθος, τοὔργον, ἐρεῖς, λαλήσει 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 4.33, compare 6.61; ἐλάλησεν ὁ κωφός NT.Matt.9.33:—\">NT+3rd c.BC+</a>]<i>passive</i>, λαληθήσεταί σοι ὅ τι σε δεῖ ποιεῖν <b>it shall be told</b> thee.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Act.9.6. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>chatter</b>, opposed to articulate speech, as of locusts, <b>chirp</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 5.34 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; μεσημβρίας λαλεῖν τέττιξ (i.e. εἰμί), a very grasshopper to <b>chirp</b> at midday, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristopho Comicus 10.6; ἀνθρωπίνως λ. 3rd c.BC(?): Strato Comicus 1.46. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> of musical sounds, αὐλῷ λαλέω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 20.29 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; of trees,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" see.above 1.2; δι᾽[αὐλοῦ ἢ σάλπιγγος] λ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Audibilibus” 801a29 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of Echo, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 74.14: also c._accusative_ _cognate_, μάγαδιν λαλεῖν\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <b>sound</b> the μάγαδις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Anaxandrides Comicus 35. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2980","accentedUnicode":"λαλέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0215","matchingForm":"ἀλάλητος","stepTransliteration":"alalētos","gloss":"inexpressible","_zh_tw_Gloss":"用說不出來","_es_Gloss":"inexpresable","_zh_Gloss":"用说不出来"},{"strongNumber":"G0216","matchingForm":"ἄλαλος","stepTransliteration":"alalos","gloss":"mute","_zh_tw_Gloss":"啞吧","_es_Gloss":"mudo","_zh_Gloss":"哑吧"},{"strongNumber":"G2981","matchingForm":"λαλιά","stepTransliteration":"lalia","gloss":"speech","_zh_tw_Gloss":"話","_es_Gloss":"discurso","_zh_Gloss":"话"},{"strongNumber":"G3004G","matchingForm":"λέγω","stepTransliteration":"legō","gloss":"to speak","_zh_tw_Gloss":"說","_es_Gloss":"decir","_zh_Gloss":"说"},{"strongNumber":"G3004H","matchingForm":"λέγω","stepTransliteration":"legō","gloss":"to speak: call","_zh_tw_Gloss":"說","_es_Gloss":"decir","_zh_Gloss":"说"}],"shortDef":"to speak, talk","mediumDef":"to speak, talk <br /><b>to make vocal utterance; to babble, to talk;</b>, in NT <i>absolute</i> <b>to exercise the faculty of speech,</b> <ref='Mat.9.33'>Mt. 9:33</ref>; <b>to speak,</b> <ref='Mat.10.20'>Mt. 10:20</ref>; <b>to hold converse with, to talk with,</b> <ref='Mat.12.46'>Mt. 12:46</ref>; <ref='Mrk.6.50'>Mk. 6:50</ref>; <ref='Rev.1.12'>Rev. 1:12;</ref> <b>to discourse, to make an address,</b> <ref='Luk.11.37'>Lk. 11:37</ref>; <ref='Act.11.20'>Acts 11:20;</ref> 21:39; <b>to make announcement, to make a declaration,</b> <ref='Luk.1.55'>Lk. 1:55</ref>; <b>to make mention,</b> <ref='Jhn.12.41'>Jn. 12:41</ref>; <ref='Act.2.31'>Acts 2:31;</ref> <ref='Heb.4.8'>Heb. 4:8;</ref> <ref='2Pe.3.16'>2Pet. 3:16;</ref> <i>transitive</i> <b>to speak, address, preach,</b> <ref='Mat.9.18'>Mt. 9:18</ref>; <ref='Jhn.3.11'>Jn. 3:11</ref>; <ref='Tit.2.1'>Tit. 2:1;</ref> <b>to give utterance to, utter,</b> <ref='Mr